            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>Telecom equipment provider Ericsson has launched legal actions against Chinese company Transsion in Brazil, India, Nigeria, and before the Unified Patent Court, according to Bloomberg News.</p><p>\n\nThe company describes Transsion as the last major smartphone manufacturer lacking a global patent license, and claims that for nearly a decade, Transsion has dismissed Ericsson's FRAND (Fair, Reasonable, and Non-Discriminatory) offers. Ericsson states that Transsion's delays are hampering the innovation cycle and distorting competition for licensed players.</p></div>",
